During a press briefing, Press Secretary Jay Carney addressed various topics, including the potential nomination of Jack Lew as Treasury Secretary, the debt ceiling, gun control, and the situation in Syria. Carney did not provide a definitive answer regarding the use of the 14th Amendment or the minting of a trillion-dollar coin to address the debt ceiling. He emphasized that Congress has the responsibility to raise the debt ceiling and that the President will not negotiate over it. Carney also stated that the President is committed to taking action on immigration reform early in his second term.